<h1> Easy Bake Recipes: Pancakes </h1>
<p> American Style Buttermilk Pancakes Recipe:

    100g plain flour
    2tsp baking powder
    1/2 tsp bicarbonate of soda
    1tbsp golden caster sugar
    2 large eggs, separated
    284ml Buttermilk
    25g butter, melted and extra butter

    First sift the flour, baking powder, bicarbonate of soda, sugar and a pinch of salt into a bowl.
    Whisk the egg whites until stiff peaks form. Then mix the yolks, buttermilk and melted butter and whisk in the flour mix until batter thickens.
    Then fold the egg whites into the batter until evenly mixed.
    Then heat a large frying pan and add melted butter. Place 3 large spoons of batter into the pan to make 10cm diameter pancakes. When bubbles appear after 3 minutes flip the
    pancakes over and cook until browned. Then top with syrup, raspberries and berries. </p>

  <h1> Easy Bake Recipes: Vanilla Cake Recipe:  <h1>

<p> 200g caster sugar
    200g softened butter
    4 eggs, beaten
    200g self-raising flour
    1 tsp baking powder
    2 tbsp milk,
    Vanilla Essence, 5 drops

    Heat oven to 190C/fan 170C/gas 5. Butter a 20cm sandwich tin and line with non-stick baking paper.
    In a large bowl, beat 200g caster sugar, vanilla essence, 200g softened butter, 4 beaten eggs, 200g self-raising flour, 1 tsp baking powder
    and 2 tbsp milk together until you have a smooth, soft batter. Add the mixture in the tin, smooth the surface with a
    spatula or the back of a spoon. Bake for about 20 mins until golden and the cake springs back when pressed. Turn onto a cooling
    rack and leave to cool completely. Then decorate with icing and cherries. </p>


